pgTitle: List of MPs elected in the 1708 British general election

rows.text:
Lord Haddo - ineligible as son of Scottish peer
Replaced by Sir Alexander Cumming 1709

Sir Simon Harcourt - unseated on petition
Replaced by William Hucks 1709

Sir Henry Peachey, Bt - sat for Sussex
Replaced by Viscount Lumley 1708

Hon. Henry Herbert - succeeded to peerage
Replaced by Charles Cornwall 1709

The 1st Viscount Windsor - unseated on petition
Replaced by William Hale Jan 1709.

William Shippen - unseated on petition
Replaced by Sir Cleave More, Bt Jan 1709.

Sir Jeffrey Jeffreys - died
Replaced by Edward Jeffreys 1709

Sir Thomas Felton, Bt - died
Replaced by Joseph Weld 1709

Dugald Stewart - resigned
Replaced by John Montgomerie 1710
Samuel Shepheard - Election void, but re-elected 1710

Lewis Pryse -sat for Cardiganshire
Replaced by Simon Harcourt 1710
Allen Bathurst - Election void, but re-elected 1709
Charles Coxe - Election void, but re-elected 1709

Sir Thomas Parker - resigned
Replaced by Richard Pye 1710

John Churchill - died
Replaced by Denis Bond 1710

Lord Johnstone - ineligible as eldest son of a Scottish peer
Replaced by Sir William Grierson, Bt 1709

Sir Charles Blois, Bt - unseated on petition
Replaced by Sir Richard Allin, Bt 1709.

Robert Kemp - unseated on petition
Replaced by Daniel Harvey 1709

Hon. John Sinclair - ineligible as the eldest son of a Scottish peer
Replaced by James Abercrombie 1710

Sir Samuel MacClellan - died
Replaced by Sir Patrick Johnston 1709

Patrick Moncreiff -died
Replaced by Sir Robert Anstruther 1710

William Cooke - died
Replaced by Francis Wyndham 1709

Hon. Roger Townshend died
Replaced by Nathaniel Symonds

Viscount Woodstock - succeeded to peerage
Replaced by Thomas Jervoise 1709

Sir John Leake - sat for Rochester
Replaced by Kenrick Edisbury 1708

Thomas Onslow - sat for Bletchingley
Replaced by Nicholas Carew 1708

Hon. William Ashburnham - succeeded to peerage
Replaced by John Ashburnham

Viscount Rialton - sat for Oxfordshire
Replaced by Sir John Evelyn, Bt 1708

Sir Stephen Lennard - died
Replaced by David Polhill 1710

Peter Gott - sat for Sussex
Replaced by Samuel Gott 1708

Lord Johnstone - ineligible as son of Scottish peer
Replaced by John Houstoun 1708

Joseph Addison - unseated on petition
Replaced by Francis Robartes 1709.

James Kendall - unseated on petition
Replaced by Russell Robartes 1709 - sat for Bodmin
Replaced by Horatio Walpole 1710

Hon. Henry Mordaunt - died
Replaced by Joseph Addison 1710

Earl of Hertford - sat for Northumberland
Replaced by Edward Ernle, Bt 1708

Sir John Wolstenholme - died
Replaced by John Austen 1708

Robert Orme - election voided
Replaced by Thomas Meredyth, Mar 1709

Thomas Medlycott - sat for Westminster
Replaced by Thomas Smith 1709

Anthony Hammond - ineligible to sit
Replaced by Sir Gregory Page, Bt 1708

William Harris - died
Replaced by Christopher Harris 1709

Sir Edward Turnour - unseated on petition
Replaced by William Thompson, Jan 1709

Sir Robert Jenkinson - died
Replaced by Sir Robert Jenkinson 1710

Thomas Erle - sat for Wareham
Replaced by Sir Thomas Littleton 1708

Hugh Rose - election void
Replaced by Charles Rosse 1710

James Buller - sat for Cornwall
Replaced by Sir Cholmeley Dering 1710

John Kynaston - unseated on petition
Replaced by Sir Edward Leighton, Bt, Dec 1709

Richard Mytton - unseated on petition
Not replaced.

John Prowse - died
Replaced by Sir William Wyndham 1710

Viscount Woodstock - sat for Hampshire
Replaced by Simeon Stuart 1708

Lord Strathnaver - ineligible as eldest son of a Scotch peer
Replaced by Robert Douglas 1709

Sir Godfrey Copley - died
Replaced by Leonard Smelt 1709

Hon. James Brydges - sat for Hereford
Replaced by Robert Furnese 1708

William Jennens - died
Replaced by Thomas Renda 1709

Thomas Ellys - died
Replaced by Henry Grey 1709

Hon. Henry Thynne - sat for Weymouth and Melcombe Regis
Replaced by Henry Gorges 1708

Hon. Henry Thynne - died
Replaced by Edward Clavell 1709

Frederick Tylney - election void
Replaced by Richard Wollaston, Dec 1708

Thomas Lewis- election void
Replaced by George William Brydges, Dec 1708

George Lockhart - sat for Edinburghshire
Replaced by William Cochrane 1708

George Dodington - sat for Bridgwater
Replaced by Robert Bristow 1708
